Joseph MATCHOK, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 7139. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 21, 1933. Joseph Matchok, in pro. per. H. T. Nichols, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and HUTCHESON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On the authority of Albrecht v. United States, 273 U. S. 1, 47 S. Ct. 250, 71 L. Ed. 505, and of United States v. Daugherty, 269 U. S. 360, 46 S. Ct. 156, 70 L. Ed. 309, the judgment is affirmed.
